children.subject: I have only taken Math 110, and I can tell you that Math 110 is pretty light (just like your typical math class). There are weekly psets, midterms/final, and maybe some quizzes here and there.

I am taking 110 this semester and took 161 last spring. Both were light. If Stankova is teaching it next semester (which I heard she is), you should take it as she is arguably the best teacher in the math department (disclaimer: I had pretty bad math professors before).

history.content: I'm planning to take CS 161, CS 174, and Math 110 next semester and would like to get an idea of what the workloads for these classes are like and if it would be reasonable to take all three in the same semester. Any advice would be appreciated!
history.subject: CS 161, CS 174, Math 110
